  "body_html": "<div>Knowledge of the axilla is expected by the RCEM as set out in section 9.1.1.2 of the syllabus.<br /><br />Candidates are expected to have the following knowledge:<br /><br /><ul><li>Surface anatomy, nerve supply and action of subscapularis and Teres Major</li><li>Knowledge the axilla transmits the brachial plexus</li><li>Knowledge that the axillary artery supplies the humeral circumflex arteries</li><li>Knowledge of the brachial plexus</li></ul><br /><i>Diagram illustrating position of Teres Major muscle (posterior view)</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb001b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb001.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teres major'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb001b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><i>Diagram illustrating position of Subscapularis (anterior view)</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb002b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb002.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subscapularis muscle'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><t